23/03/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The new government of Recep Tayyip Erdogan easily won a vote of confidence by parliament on Sunday (23 March). The vote was 350-162; 38 members did not vote. Erdogan took over the post of prime minister two weeks ago with the support of the ruling Justice and Development Party. Immediately after the vote, he promised to work hard to resolve the problems of the country and to overcome these "difficult days". (Turkish Daily News, AFP - 23/03/03)
